body: use protobuf lite

It occurs when all of the below apply:
1. Link to protobuf dynamically 
2. Use full libprotobuf instead of the lite one
3. The same protobuf definition was used in multiple DSO(or DLLs). For example, pytorch/onnx/onnxruntime may all have onnx.TensorProto.

@snnn Thanks, will try.
Do you know what causes the regression in master comparing to 1.4.0?
@xkszltl sorry I don't know. Could you please help us dig more? It shouldn't cause such difference.
This is where I end up with after setting `-Donnxruntime_USE_FULL_PROTOBUF=OFF`: Seems onnx-tensorrt wants full protobuf.
Yes, tensorrt doesn't support protobuf-lite.

I tried art's unit tests. Not all failed, part of them reported the onnx-ml protobuf issue while others passed. And I'm also seeing crashes in trt. I think it is related to the TRT refactoring.  As you can see now there is a separated shared lib: libonnxruntime_providers_tensorrt.so. 
In 1.4.0, TRT is part of libonnxruntime.so, so at least everything inside onnxruntime is consistent.

I guess you were using protobuf from a shared lib?

Yes.
We have protobuf as shared lib used:
1. directly by our code
2. linked by ort
3. through other libs like pytorch, grpc, ...

Any progress on this?
Seems the issue is still there.

@xkszltl I believe you're using the onnxruntime_PREFER_SYSTEM_LIB cmake option to build ORT. This option is experimental in that we don't support it fully. Moreover, if onnxruntime_PREFER_SYSTEM_LIB and onnxruntime_USE_FULL_PROTOBUF are ON, then protobuf_USE_STATIC_LIBS must be turned ON too.

What's the reason of enforcing `Protobuf_USE_STATIC_LIBS=ON` with system protobuf?
I thought it's to avoid extra deps when delivery (but we ship our protobuf as well) so I bypassed that check.

That doesn't work.

- `libonnxruntime.so`
- `libonnxruntime_providers_tensorrt.so`.
- `onnxruntime_pybind11_state.so`

`libonnxruntime_providers_tensorrt.so` triggered the issue when it's loaded.

If onnx-ml are compiled into to `.so` and loaded to the same address space, this issue is expected to happen.

I don't know how the default build script works.
Maybe a special combination happen to shadow the issue.

If proto file need to be used in multiple `.so` linked together, it should be compiled into a separated `.so` to avoid re-registration.

I've sent a PR for to build onnx-ml as `.so`.
